1. apt install vim

2. apt install cscope, or install from source code

3. apt install ctags, or install from source code

4. add the flowing code to ~/.bashrc
alias vi='vim'
alias cs='ctags -R * && cscope -Rbq'

export echo=echo
export EDITOR=vim

5. cp -R ./vim ~/.vim

6. cp ./vimrc ~/.vimrc

7. logout then login

8. enter the top directory of source code, run common 'cs' which may take a few minutes

9. open source file from top directory, such as vim x.c or vim x/y/z.c

10. common commands
ctrl+[, enter the sub function / variable definition
ctrl+\+c, show the caller function
ctrl+\+s, show the postions of the function or the string
